															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/troyl" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(451071); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=451071&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610250823" alt="TroyL" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=451071)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/troyl" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(451071); return false;" >TroyL</a></span> <span class="odate time_1359603713 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">31 Jan 2013 03:41</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1699436">
									

<p>The Ultimate Warrior, alias Jim Hellwig, was one of the worst wrestlers of all time. Not because he didn't know how to wrestle (he wasn't that good) or because he didn't know how to work a crowd (he did), but because he didn't appreciate anything that he was given as a performer.</p>
<p>Excellent wrestlers like Rick Rude or Randy Savage were the ones working their asses off to make him look half-way decent. This totally should have been Able versus The Undertakers. Two people who die and just <em>keep getting back up again</em>. The Urn versus SCP-072? That would have been friggin' excellent.</p>
<p>As it is.. It's not bad, and I could have really done without the Blackwood reference, but&#8230;</p>
<p>Jesus. This thing made me just grin the entire time. I think you really had to grow up with a lot of this to appreciate it at all.</p>
<p>So&#8230; Sure. +1.</p>
<p>Don't make me regret this.</p>

							</div>

