		<div class="post" id="post-1700113">
		<div class="long">
			<div class="head">
									<div class="options">
						<a href="javascript:;" onclick="togglePostFold(event,1700113)" class="btn btn-default btn-small btn-sm">Fold</a>
					</div>
								<div class="title" id="post-title-1700113">
																		
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/tl333s" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1304786); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1304786&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610250823" alt="TL333s" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1304786)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/tl333s" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1304786); return false;" >TL333s</a></span> <span class="odate time_1359677245 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">01 Feb 2013 00:07</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1700113">
									

<p>This takes me back to the time in college when I actually watched pro wrestling. I enjoyed it more once I realized it was a soap opera based on ridiculous levels of machismo. Unrelated, this was also the same time that I watched the single season of DragonBall Z I ever saw, which I now realize I enjoyed for similar reasons. All the ridiculousness is there, even if I don't recognize half of the wrestlers.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>ALL THOSE WHO FACE ME SHALL FALL LIKE DOMINOS ON A CHESS BOARD BEFORE THE MIGHT OF MY MONOPOLY!</p>
</blockquote>
<p>This is brilliant. And also in character.</p>
<p>This is the best thing since the Able/682 rap battle. I am not even kidding.</p>

